==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: onychophoran
<hw>onychophoran</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>Any of numerous velvety-skinned
wormlike carnivorous animals common in tropical forests having
characteristics of both arthropods and annelid worms; a member of the
<class>Onychophora</class>, also called <class>Malacopoda</class>. See
<er>Malacopoda</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> velvet worm, peripatus.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>onymous</ent>⟦br⟧
